oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Sheet Music General Grant's March by Edward Mack
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Geneal Grant's March was composed by Edward Mack (1821-1882) in 1862. Mack immigrated to the United States from Germany around 1831. He entered the Philadelphia School for the Blind in 1844.; He composed several songs during the Civil War era including McClellan'sGrand March and Buell's March. This particular printing of sheet music dates from around 1924 from Eclipse Publishing.
